{"action": "edit", "code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    mypink = np.array([[0, 1, 0], [1, 0, 1], [0, 1, 0]])\n    myred = np.array([[1, 0, 1], [0, 1, 0], [1, 0, 1]])\n    mygreen = np.array([[0, 1, 1], [0, 1, 1], [1, 0, 0]])\n    myblue = np.array([[1, 1, 0], [1, 0, 1], [0, 1, 0]])\n    non_black = make_non_black_pixels_one(input_grid)\n    output_grid = color_non_black_pixels(mypink, myred, mygreen, myblue, non_black)\n    return output_grid\ndef make_non_black_pixels_one(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    non_black = np.where(input_grid != black, 1, 0)\n    return non_black\ndef color_non_black_pixels(mypink: np.ndarray, myred: np.ndarray, mygreen: np.ndarray, myblue: np.ndarray, non_black: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes in four numpy arrays representing pink, red, green, and blue colors and a numpy array representing non-black pixels.\n    It returns a numpy array where non-black pixels are colored based on the following conditions:\n    - If a non-black pixel is the same as mypink, it is colored pink.\n    - If a non-black pixel is the same as myred, it is colored red.\n    - If a non-black pixel is the same as mygreen, it is colored green.\n    - If a non-black pixel is the same as myblue, it is colored blue.\n    \"\"\"\n    output_grid = np.zeros_like(non_black)\n    output_grid = np.where(non_black == mypink, pink, output_grid)\n    output_grid = np.where(non_black == myred, red, output_grid)\n    output_grid = np.where(non_black == mygreen, green, output_grid)\n    output_grid = np.where(non_black == myblue, blue, output_grid)\n    return output_grid", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    mypink = np.array([[0,1,0],[1,0,1],[0,1,0]])\n    myred = np.array([[1,0,1],[0,1,0],[1,0,1]])\n    mygreen = np.array([[0,1,1],[0,1,1],[1,0,0]])\n    myblue = np.array([[1,1,0],[1,0,1],[0,1,0]])\n    non_black = `make all non black pixels 1`(input_grid)\n    output_grid = `if n